Package ca.openosp.openo.rx.erx.model

Class ERxPrescription

java.lang.Object
ca.openosp.openo.rx.erx.model.ERxPrescription
public class ERxPrescription extends Object
A value type that stores the prescription data sent by the External Prescriber.

    • ERxPrescription

      public ERxPrescription(String doctorLicenseNo, String patientId, String prescriptionId, boolean isDCPrescription, String discontinuedPrescriptionId, String discontinuedUntil, boolean isRenewal, String renewedPrescriptionId, String prescriptionDateTime, String productName, String productForm, String productStrength, long drugCode, float quantity, int qtyUnitId, String qtyUnitToString, int refills, int refillsDuration, PrescriptionTimeUnit refillsDurationTimeUnit, String sigManual, float sigDosage, int sigUnitId, String sigUnitToString, int sigFrequencyId, String sigFrequencyToString, int sigSpecifierId, String sigSpecifierToString, boolean sigPRN, int treatmentDuration, PrescriptionTimeUnit treatmentDurationTimeUnit, String instructions, String manualPrescriptionContent, int narcoticInterval, PrescriptionTimeUnit narcoticIntervalTimeUnit, float narcoticTotalQuantity, String status, PrescriptionStatusId statusID, String ceasingReason, boolean dispenseAsWritten, int dosageVariationIndicator, String endingDate, String lastModifiedByName, String lastModifiedDate, String prescriptionEstimatedEndDate, String formattedPrescriptionToString, String prescriptionToString)
      Construct a ERxPrescription.
      Parameters:
      doctorLicenseNo - Physician's license number issued by a regulatory body.
      patientId - A unique identifier for the patient, as set by the External Prescription software.
      prescriptionId - A unique identifier for the prescription.
      isDCPrescription - TRUE if this prescription is of type Discontinuation/Ceasing; FALSE otherwise.
      discontinuedPrescriptionId - References the original prescriptionId that is being discontinued/ceased.
      discontinuedUntil - Specifies the date that the prescription will be re-activated on. If given, will be in the format "YYYY-MM-DD".
      isRenewal - TRUE if the prescription is of type Renewal; FALSE otherwise.
      renewedPrescriptionId - References the original prescriptionId that is being renewed.
      prescriptionDateTime - Represents the date the prescription was made by the physician. If given, will be in the format "YYYY-MM-DD".
      productName - The (localized) brand name of the drug that is being prescribed.
      productForm - The (localized) form in which the prescribed drug will be served.
      productStrength - The quantity of drug in its form.
      drugCode - A identification code for the drug.
      quantity - The quantity to dispense.
      qtyUnitId - The dispense quantity qualifier.
      qtyUnitToString - A (localized) string representing the qtyUnitId interpretation.
      refills - The number of repeats.
      refillsDuration - can be specified as a duration, which defines how long the refill is expected to last.
      sigManual - Contains the prescription's sig (i.e.: instructions on how to take the drug) if manually entered by the physician.
      sigDosage - Represents the quantity of product in its form.
      sigUnitId -
      sigUnitToString - A (localized) string representing the sigUnitId interpretation.
      sigFrequencyId - The frequency at which the drug must be administered.
      sigFrequencyToString - A (localized) string containing the sigFrequencyId interpretation.
      sigSpecifierId - Additionnal SIG information.
      sigSpecifierToString - A (localized) string representing the sigSpecifierId .
      sigPRN - TRUE if this drug must be administered only if necessary; FALSE otherwise.
      treatmentDuration - The duration of one dispense.
      treatmentDurationTimeUnit - This field combines with treatmentDuration .
      instructions - Manually entered instructions by the physician.
      manualPrescriptionContent - If the prescription is of type manual, this field contains direct text input from the physician.
      narcoticInterval - The time interval at which the narcoticTotalQuantity must be served.
      narcoticIntervalTimeUnit - This field combines with narcoticInterval .
      narcoticTotalQuantity - The total quantity to be served at the specified narcoticInterval .
      status - A (localized) string representing the statusID.
      statusID - The current status of this prescription.
      ceasingReason - A (localized) string stating the reason why the prescription was discontinued/ceased.
      dispenseAsWritten - TRUE if the prescription must be dispensed as written (i.e.: if a generic drug could not substitute the actual prescribed drug); FALSE otherwise.
      dosageVariationIndicator - 1 means the prescribing physician is specifying an increase in dosage;

      -1 = means the prescribing physician is specifying a decrease in dosage;

      0 = means the prescribing physician has not specified any variation

      endingDate - An ending date specified by the prescribing physician. Will have the form "YYYY-MM-DD".
      lastModifiedByName - If a prescription is modified, this field contains the physician's full name.
      lastModifiedDate - When the prescription is modified, this field contains the last modified date. Will have the form YYYY-MM-DD
      prescriptionEstimatedEndDate - A calculated, estimated ending date for this prescription.
      formattedPrescriptionToString - Contains a formattted textual version of the prescription.
      prescriptionToString - Contains an unformatted textual version of the prescription.
